Thousands of years before the development of Western Medicine, the ancient Chinese herbalist Shennanog recorded the healing properties of the jujube berries (also known as Chinese dates). He referred to the jujube as an almost miraculous health tonic and prescribed it to nourish the blood, liver and stomach.

Jujube berry is very rich in nutrients including vitamin C, vitamin A, beta-carotene, vitamin E, vitamin B1, B2, bioflavonoid and contains high concentration of calcium, iron, magnesium, potassium and zinc

Cajun Blend: onion, thyme, mustard seed, sweet paprika, black pepper, red pepper, hot paprika.

Curry Powder (Mild): coriander seed, cumin seed, fennel seed, brown mustard seed, black pepper, turmeric.

Mexican Seasoning: savoury leaf, onion, sweet pepper, garlic, cumin, hot pepper.

Middle Eastern Blend: turmeric, garlic, cumin, paprika, black pepper, coriander seed, onion, cinnamon.

Mixed Spice: coriander seed, cinnamon, ginger, caraway seed, nutmeg, cloves.

Tuscan Salt Rub: salt, onion, garlic, sweet paprika, marjoram, white pepper, basil, thyme.
